// 01


About Me


&lt;div class="about-text"&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;
    I'm a &lt;strong&gt;Mechatronics Engineer&lt;/strong&gt; with a strong background in
    automation, control systems, and electrical engineering. My career started
    in Ecuador, where I worked as an &lt;strong&gt;Electrical Engineer&lt;/strong&gt; in
    a ceramic plant — programming PLCs, maintaining industrial motors, and
    keeping production lines running. I then moved into
    &lt;strong&gt;Quality Control&lt;/strong&gt;, evaluating X-ray medical equipment
    against national regulations for Inglemed.
  &lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;
    Today, based in &lt;strong&gt;New York City&lt;/strong&gt;, I work as a
    &lt;strong&gt;Service Engineer at Ecolab&lt;/strong&gt;, designing digital maintenance
    systems and troubleshooting complex electromechanical equipment for
    enterprise clients. In parallel, I'm completing my
    &lt;strong&gt;M.S. in Applied Artificial Intelligence at Baruch College&lt;/strong&gt;,
    combining my engineering foundation with machine learning, deep learning,
    and data analytics.
  &lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;
    My goal is to bridge the gap between physical systems and intelligent
    software — building solutions that are both technically robust and
    data-informed.
  &lt;/p&gt;
